Fix compiler-rt libatomic handling on the cross MSVC target.

Two atomics-related problems break the `x86_64-pc-windows-msvc` compiler-rt
(`-libc`) build:

1. `withAtomicsPthread` defaults on whenever the release is >= 19 and
   `stdenv.cc.libc != null`, which is true for the MSVC cross target. That
   passes `-DCOMPILER_RT_LIBATOMIC_USE_PTHREAD=ON`, defining
   `_LIBATOMIC_USE_PTHREAD`, so `lib/builtins/atomic.c` does `#include
   <pthread.h>` -- a header that does not exist on the MSVC target -- failing
   with `fatal error: 'pthread.h' file not found`. atomic.c falls back to a
   non-pthread lock when the macro is unset, so disable it on Windows.

2. The `postInstall` that aliases the standalone libatomic DSO is hardcoded for
   ELF `.so` names (`libclang_rt.atomic-*.so`). On Windows the library is built
   as `clang_rt.atomic_dynamic-*.dll`, so the glob matches nothing; with the
   build's `nullglob` the second `ln -s $out/lib/*/libclang_rt.atomic-*.so
   $out/lib/` collapses to `ln -s $out/lib/`, which tries to create `./lib` and
   fails with `ln: failed to create symbolic link './lib': File exists`. These
   `.so` aliases are meaningless on Windows, so skip them there (the atomic
   DLL/import lib is still installed).

--- a/pkgs/development/compilers/llvm/common/compiler-rt/default.nix
+++ b/pkgs/development/compilers/llvm/common/compiler-rt/default.nix
@@ -36,7 +36,8 @@
   # implementation of the routines instead of the implementation
   # using ad-hoc mutexes (which doesn't depend on libc at all).
   # Use of pthreads helps code play better with sanitizers.
-  withAtomicsPthread ? lib.versionAtLeast release_version "19" && stdenv.cc.libc != null,
+  withAtomicsPthread ?
+    lib.versionAtLeast release_version "19" && stdenv.cc.libc != null && !stdenv.hostPlatform.isWindows,
 
   # In recent releases, the compiler-rt build seems to produce
   # many `libclang_rt*` libraries, but not a single unified
@@ -285,7 +286,7 @@
     + lib.optionalString forceLinkCompilerRt ''
       ln -s $out/lib/*/libclang_rt.builtins-*.a $out/lib/libcompiler_rt.a
     ''
-    + lib.optionalString (withAtomics && withAtomicsLib) ''
+    + lib.optionalString (withAtomics && withAtomicsLib && !stdenv.hostPlatform.isWindows) ''
       ln -s $out/lib/*/libclang_rt.atomic-*.so $out/lib/libatomic.so
       # create a link with the original soname as well, so it's found at runtime
       ln -s $out/lib/*/libclang_rt.atomic-*.so $out/lib/
